episodes.title: Broke His Crown
episodes.plot: Ice King has some problems with his crown. Princess Bubblegum helps along with Marceline.

episodes.title: Don't Look
episodes.plot: At the library, Finn learns of a mountain with treasure possessing transformative properties at its peak. He and Jake venture to find the treasure, but find more than they expected when they encounter the hermit guarding the treasure.

episodes.title: Beyond the Grotto
episodes.plot: In pursuit of a runaway Sea Lard, Finn and Jake are led down a whirlpool to a curious new land.

episodes.title: Lady Rainicorn of the Crystal Dimension
episodes.plot: T.V., still living with his mother, discovers a magical object and without knowing, attracts Lee - a rainicorn from the Crystal Dimension, which reveals an important part of Lady Rainicorn's past.

episodes.title: I Am a Sword
episodes.plot: Fin loses his Fin-Sword and he needs to get it back ASAP, because someone is using it to cause terror and rampage.

episodes.title: Bun Bun
episodes.plot: Princess Bubblegum feels sad that Cinnamon Bun is the only candy person in the Flame Kingdom, so she creates Bun Bun, a tiny cinnamon bun, to keep him company.

episodes.title: Normal Man
episodes.plot: Stripped of his magic powers, Normal Man enlists Finn and Jake's help to rescue his brother Glob.

episodes.title: Elemental
episodes.plot: Ice King discovers something buried deep beneath the Ice Kingdom that could change Ooo forever.

episodes.title: Five Short Tables
episodes.plot: Fionna and Cake go on an adventure to push the art of cake to another level.

episodes.title: The Music Hole
episodes.plot: Finn gets to be the judge of battle of the bands held in the Candy Kingdom, when he starts to hear music that nobody else can.

episodes.title: Daddy-Daughter Card Wars
episodes.plot: Daddy-Daughter Card Wars: To put his embarrassing past behind him, Jake needs his daughter Charlie's help to win an underground Card Wars tourney.

episodes.title: Preboot
episodes.plot: While searching for old human artifacts, Jake, Finn, and Susan Strong meet Tiffany, who is employed by a mysterious Doctor Gross.

episodes.title: Reboot
episodes.plot: After Susan Strong's chip is activated, she goes rogue and attacks Finn.

episodes.title: Two Swords
episodes.plot: Finn and Jake puzzle over the nature of a mysterious newcomer.

episodes.title: Do No Harm
episodes.plot: Doctor Princess thrusts a great responsibility upon Finn. Jake goes adventuring with a new friend.

episodes.title: Wheels
episodes.plot: Kim Kil Whan seeks Jake's assistance with his daughter's detachment from school. Jake gets distracted by something else instead.

episodes.title: High Strangeness
episodes.plot: Tree Trunks receives a strange visitor who reacquaints her with some family members. Tensions flare between her and Princess Bubblegum.

episodes.title: Horse and Ball
episodes.plot: James Baxter takes his turn to showcase his backstory through an interesting collage of flashbacks brought on by his famous Ball being popped.

episodes.title: Jelly Beans Have Power
episodes.plot: Princess Bubblegum explores her new candy powers.

episodes.title: Islands Part 1: The Invitation
episodes.plot: Consequences regarding Susan's last sent message appear at the Candy Kingdom's shore, bringing about new questions and mysteries leading Finn, Jake and Susan to embark on a new adventure.

episodes.title: Islands Part 2: Whipple the Happy Dragon
episodes.plot: After a mysterious craft lands in Ooo, Finn, Jake, Susan Strong, set sail for the Island that it originated, hoping to learn the truth about the past and what happened to the humans.

episodes.title: Islands Part 3: Mysterious Island
episodes.plot: After waking up alone and shipwrecked, Finn investigates a bizarre island in search of his friends.

episodes.title: Islands Part 4: Imaginary Resources
episodes.plot: Finn and Jake find BMO, who is enjoying newfound fame and popularity in a new land.

episodes.title: Islands Part 5: Hide and Seek
episodes.plot: Susan strong has flashbacks to her life when she was younger, and starts remembering who she actually is.

episodes.title: Islands Part 6: Min and Marty
episodes.plot: Susan drops a big surprise on Finn and questions about his past are answered.

episodes.title: Islands Part 7: Helpers
episodes.plot: Finn finally finds what he was looking for but things are not the way he expected them to be. Susan sees someone from her past life.

episodes.title: Islands Part 8: The Light Cloud
episodes.plot: Finn decides to leave the island and tries to get everyone else to come with him as well.
